{"created-date": {"value": 1671617772294}, "last-modified-date": {"value": 1671617772294}, "source": {"source-orcid": {"uri": "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9785-7726", "path": "0000-0002-9785-7726", "host": "orcid.org"}, "source-client-id": null, "source-name": {"value": "Luca Baldini"}, "assertion-origin-orcid": null, "assertion-origin-client-id": null, "assertion-origin-name": null}, "put-code": 125084238, "path": "/0000-0002-9785-7726/work/125084238", "title": {"title": {"value": "The EEE Multigap Resistive Plate Chambers as tracking devices to monitor the stability of a civil building"}, "subtitle": null, "translated-title": null}, "journal-title": {"value": "Journal of Instrumentation"}, "short-description": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n               <jats:p>Due to their efficiency, tracking capabilities and long-term\n  operational conditions, Multigap Resistive Plate Chambers (MRPC) may\n  be used in a stable location in coincidence with additional\n  detectors fixed to other parts of a civil building, to detect\n  relative displacements of different parts of the building due to\n  long term deformations of the structure. In this contribution we\n  report the results of two different measurements carried out in the\n  Department of Physics and Astronomy of the University of Catania\n  (with three floors above the ground and an underground basement),\n  using one of the MRPC telescopes of the Extreme Energy Events\n  project, in coincidence with two scintillator-based muon telescopes\n  located in various positions inside the building. Experimental\n  results obtained by these measurements campaigns over a period of\n  about three months are reported, together with a discussion about\n  the performance of the technique. The sensitivity of the method is\n  also discussed by means of Monte Carlo simulations.</jats:p>", "citation": {"citation-type": "bibtex", "citation-value": "@article{Pinto_2021,\tdoi = {10.1088/1748-0221/16/04/c04003},\turl = {https://doi.org/10.1088%2F1748-0221%2F16%2F04%2Fc04003},\tyear = 2021,\tmonth = {apr},\tpublisher = {{IOP} Publishing},\tvolume = {16},\tnumber = {04},\tpages = {C04003},\tauthor = {C. Pinto and M. Abbrescia and C. Avanzini and L. Baldini and R. Baldini Ferroli and L.G. Batignani and M. Battaglieri and S. Boi and E. Bossini and F. Carnesecchi and C. Cical{\\`{o}} and L. Cifarelli and F. Coccetti and E. Coccia and A. Corvaglia and D. De Gruttola and S. De Pasquale and L. Fabbri and L. Galante and P. Galeotti and M. Garbini and G. Gemme and I. Gnesi and S. Grazzi and D. Hatzifotiadou and P. La Rocca and Z. Liu and G. Mandaglio and G. Maron and M.N. Mazziotta and A. Mulliri and R. Nania and F. Noferini and F. Nozzoli and F. Palmonari and M. Panareo and M.P. Panetta and R. Paoletti and C. Pellegrino and L. Perasso and G. Piragino and S. Pisano and F. Riggi and G.C. Righini and C. Ripoli and M. Rizzi and G. Sartorelli and E. Scapparone and M. Schioppa and A. Scribano and M. Selvi and G. Serri and S. Squarcia and M. Taiuti and G. Terreni and A. Trifir{\\'{o}} and M. Trimarchi and M.C. Vistoli and L. Votano and M.C.S. Williams and A. Zichichi and R. Zuyeuski},\ttitle = {The {EEE} Multigap Resistive Plate Chambers as tracking devices to monitor the stability of a civil building},\tjournal = {Journal of Instrumentation}}"}, "type": "journal-article", "publication-date": {"year": {"value": "2021"}, "month": {"value": "04"}, "day": {"value": "01"}}, "external-ids": {"external-id": [{"external-id-type": "doi", "external-id-value": "10.1088/1748-0221/16/04/c04003", "external-id-normalized": {"value": "10.1088/1748-0221/16/04/c04003", "transient": true}, "external-id-normalized-error": null, "external-id-url": {"value": "https://doi.org/10.1088/1748-0221/16/04/c04003"}, "external-id-relationship": "self"}, {"external-id-type": "issn", "external-id-value": "1748-0221", "external-id-normalized": {"value": "1748-0221", "transient": true}, "external-id-normalized-error": null, "external-id-ur